# Pre-commit lint checks

Before every `git commit`, run these checks on all modified Python files and fix any errors BEFORE committing:

```bash
ruff check platform/ integrators/ --config ruff.toml
ruff format --check platform/ integrators/ --config ruff.toml
```

If `ruff check` reports errors:
1. Run `ruff check --fix platform/ integrators/ --config ruff.toml` to auto-fix what's possible
2. Manually fix remaining errors (unused imports, unsorted imports, deprecated patterns, etc.)
3. Run `ruff format platform/ integrators/ --config ruff.toml` to auto-format
4. Re-run both checks to confirm they pass
5. Only then proceed with `git add` and `git commit`

Never commit code that fails `ruff check` or `ruff format --check`.
